We also test the sensitivity of the optimal control solutions to the weight parameter A in the objective functional, that is the ratio between the costs per time unit of the isolation effort and the costs of a single new infection. From numerical simulations (see Fig. 4), we observe that, by increasing A, \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
